text: Soyuz MS-05 was a Soyuz spaceflight which launched on 28 July 2017. It transported three members of the Expedition 52 crew to the International Space Station. MS-05 was the 134th flight of a Soyuz spacecraft. The crew consisted of a Russian commander, and a European and an American flight engineer. It returned to Earth on 14 December 2017 after 139 days on orbit. ==Crew== ===Backup crew=== Crew from Soyuz MS-05 with other crew members aboard ISS ==References== Category:Crewed Soyuz missions Category:Spacecraft launched in 2017 Category:2017 in Russia Category:Spacecraft launched by Soyuz-FG rockets Category:Spacecraft which reentered in 2017
